PyRFT
Contributor license Agreement("Agreement") V1.0

In order to clarify the intellectual propertly license granted
with Contributions from any person or entity, PyRFT must
have a Contributor Licnese Agreement ("CLA") agreed to by each
Contributor. The express purpose of this license is for the
protection of both the Contributor, PyRFT, and its users;
it does not in any way change your rights to use your Contributions
for any other purpose.

Either individuals or business entities, cindlugin without limitation,
all employees or agents acting on behalf of such entity ("an Entity"),
may submit Contributions to PyRFT under this Agreement. By submitting
the Agreement in written or electronic form to PyRFT you represent
that you have the requisite Authority to bind such Entity to this
Agreement as defined below.

Please read this document carefully before agreeing to it, and print
a copy for your own records and the records of any Entity which you
represent in signing this Agreement.

1. Definitions

"You" (or "Your") shall mean the copyright owner or Entity authorized
by the copyright owner that is making this Agreement with PyRFT. For
Entities, the Entity making a Contributio and all other Entities that
control, are controlled by, or are under common control with the
Entity are considered to be a single Contributor. For the purposes of
this definition, "control" means (i) the power, direct or indirect,
to case the direction or management of such entity, whether by contract
or otherwise, or (ii) ownership of fifty person (50%) or more of the
outstanding shares, or (iii) beneficial ownership of the Entity.

"Contribution" shall mean any original work of authorship, including
any modifications or additions to an existing work, that is or has
been intentionally submitted by You to PyRFT for inclusion in, or
documetation of, any of the products owned or managed by PyRFT (the
"Work"). For the purposes of tihs defintion, "submitted" means any
form of electronic, verbal, or written communication sent to PyRFT
or its representatives, including but not limited to communication on
electronic mailing lists, source code control systems, and issue
tracking systems that are managed by, or on behalf of, PyRFT fo
the purpose of discussing and improving the Work, but excluding
communications that is conspicuously marked or otherwise designated
in writing by You as "Not a Contribution".

"Open Source License" shall mean any license approved by the
Open Source Initiative (opensource.org) that meets the published
and community approved Open Source Definition.

"Chosen Open Source License" shall mean any Open Source License
which PyRFT has decided to use.

"Licensed" shall mean the active Open Source License a Contribution
is under.

2. Grant of Copyright License

Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, You hereby grant to
PyRTF and to recipients of software distributed by PyRFT a perpetual,
worldwide, non-exclusive, no-charge, royalty-free, irrevocable copyright
license to reproduce, prepare derivative works of, publically display,
publically perform, sublicense, and distribute Your Contributions and
such derivative works under the Chosen Open Source License at the time
of the grant.

You agree that You will answer either in the affirmative or negative
should PyRFT contact you regarding changing the Chosen Open Source License
under which Your Contributions are to be Licensed.

3. Grant of Patent License

Subject to the terms and conditios of this Agreement, You hereby grant to
PyRFT and to recipients of software distributed by PyRFT a perpectual,
worldwide, non-exclusive, no-charge, royalty-free, irrevocalbe (except as
stated within this section) patent license to make, have made, use,
offer to sell, sell, import, and otherwise transfer the Work, where such 
license applies only to those patent claims licensable by You that are
necessarily infringed by Your Contribution(s) alone or by combination of
Your Contribution(s) with the Work to which such Contribution(s) was
submitted. Your furthermore agree to notify PyRFT of any patents that
you know or come to know are likely infringed by the Contribution and/or
are not licensable by You. if any entity institutes patent litigation
against You or any entity (ncluding a cross-claim or counterclaim in a
lawsuit) alleging that your Contribution, or the Work to which you
have contributed, constitutes direct or contributory patent infringement,
then any patent licenses granted to that entity under this Agreement
for that Contribution or Work shall terminate as  of the date such
litigation is filed.

4. Representations

a. If You are entering this Agreement as an individual, You represent that
You are legally entitled to grand the above license. If Your employer(s) has
rights to intellectual proeprty that You create, such as your Contributions,
You represent that You have received permission to make such Contributions on
behalf of that employer, that Your employer has waived such  rights for Your
Contributions to PyRFT, or that Your employer has executed a separate
Corporate CLA with PyRFT.

b. If you are entering this Agreement on behalf of an Entity, You represent that
You are legally entitled to grant the above license. You represent further that
each employee of the Entity that submits Contributions is authorized to submit
such Contributios on behalf of the Entity.

5. you  represent that each of your Contriubtions is Y our original creation
(see sectio 7 for submissios on behalf of others). You represent that Your
Contribution submissions include complete details of any third-party license or
other restriction(s) (including, but not limited to, related patents and
trademarks) of which You are personally aware and which are associated with
any part of Your Contributions.

6. You are not excpected to provide support for Your Contributions, except
to the extent You desire to provide support. you may provide support for
free, for a fee, or not at all. Unless required by applicable law or agreed
to in  writing, You provide your Contributios on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT
WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either epxress or implied, including,
without limitation, any warranties or conditions of TITLE, NON-INFRINGMENT,
MERCHANTABILITY, or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

7. Should You wish to submit work that is not Your original creation,
You may submit it to PyRFT separately from any Contribution, identifying
the complete details of its source and of any license or other restrictions
(including, but not limited to, related patents, trademarks, or and
license agreements) of which You are personally aware, and conspicuously
marking the work as "Submitted on behalf of a third party; [named here]".

8. You agree to notify PyRFT of any facts or circumstances of which you
become aware that would make these representations inaccurate in any respect.

Submissions of this agreement are acceptable via electronic or written forms.
Electronic forms may be through an approved website system, or via a
